{"word":"παραρρήγνυμι","slug":"παραρρήγνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παραρρήγνυμι</b></el> <el>(or <el>-ύω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ρήξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to break at the side</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>to break</i> a line of battle, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; and in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be broken</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, aor2 <el>παρερράγην [ᾰ]</el>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> 2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>παρέρρωγα</el>, <i>to break</i> or <i>burst at the side</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>φωνὴ παρερρωγυῖα</el> a voice <i>broken</i> (by passion), <b><a href='S:Theophrastus'>Theophr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}